job_description:
This is Adyen

Adyen is the financial technology platform of choice for leading companies. By providing end-to-end payments capabilities, data-driven insights, and financial products in a single global

solution, Adyen helps businesses achieve their ambitions faster. With offices around the world, Adyen works with the likes of Facebook, Uber, H&M, eBay, and Microsoft. To maintain our momentum, we need people to join us in finding new ways of solving our unique challenges - people like you.

Partnerships Manager, Alternative Payment Methods

We are looking for a commercially minded person who is flexible, thoughtful, eager to tackle the problem in front of them while balancing with the business strategy. In this role you will join the Payment solution in Amsterdam, as a Payment Partnerships Manager, focusing on expanding our offer and improving our alternative payment methods, becoming the go-to expert of a specific region.

The role requires commercial and technical skills to manage a portfolio of payment methods, to fully own the relationships with the underlying partners and to connect with the commercial team (Sales and Account Management), internal stakeholders (Country Managers, Technical Support, Product marketing).

The ideal candidate thrives on a diverse role across the entire lifecycle of a product to achieve Adyen's Product strategy through conception, implementation, launch and iteration.

What you'll do

End-to-end responsibility for a set of payment methods: Act as the first point-of-contact for a portfolio of Alternative Payment Methods, taking full ownership internally as well as externally. Work with cross-functional/office colleagues as well as the Payment method partners to achieve all aspects of the product. This includes making sure Payment methods perform optimally on the Adyen platform;
Commercial Guidance: Grasp the commercial offers most effective for your market segment, guide and challenge the Commercial team on their merchant adoption and usage;
Negotiate the best value with the partner (including feature set needed for our merchants as well as pricing);
Identify and scope what new payment methods we have to offer, and how they would fit into Adyen's overall product offering;
Knowledge sharing: Enable the rest of the organization to use all aspects of the Adyen product you are managing to the maximum, by passing on your knowledge including technical (features), commercial (pricing) and competition;
Collaborating with the technical Product manager on new integrations, developments, new features and bug fixes. Being an active part of the prioritization;
Project Tracking and Implementation: Be the driving force behind proper project tracking and the continual implementation of needed tasks; ensure that there is a source of truth for the tasks at hand.

Who you are

At least 3-5 years of experience in an account management or partnerships role;
Previous experience seeing projects through from beginning to end and owning the entire process;
Exceptional people skills and the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside of Adyen;
Ability to work seamlessly with a global, multicultural team;
Proven record of high performance managing complex initiatives to achieve outstanding results. A strong understanding of the importance of data, providing actionable insights, and tracking the success of those initiatives.
Experience in a Product Management role is a strong plus;
Experience with programming and/or data analysis is a plus
Experience with payments is a plus

Our Diversity, Equity and Inclusion commitments

Our unique approach is a product of our diverse perspectives. This diversity of backgrounds and cultures is essential in helping us maintain our momentum. Our business and technical challenges are unique, and we need as many different voices as possible to join us in solving them - voices like yours. No matter who you are or where you're from, we welcome you to be your true self at Adyen.

Studies show that women and members of underrepresented communities apply for jobs only if they meet 100% of the qualifications. Does this sound like you? If so, Adyen encourages you to reconsider and apply. We look forward to your application.


What's next?

Ensuring a smooth and enjoyable candidate experience is critical for us. We aim to get back to you regarding your application within 5 business days. Our interview process tends to take about 4 weeks to complete, but may fluctuate depending on the role. Learn more about our hiring process here. Don't be afraid to let us know if you need more flexibility.

